oes ISIS stand for, what does Daesh mean and what is the right name for the terrorist organisation?</h1></section><div class="article__subdeck t-p-border-color"><p>The twisted terror thugs who rampaged across Iraq and Syria and orchestrated attacks worldwide go under several guises</p>
</div></header><div class="article__meta"><div class="article__name-date"><div class="article__author"><ul class="t-p-color article__noLabel article__ul" itemProp="author"><li class="article__author-list t-p-background-color__before"><span class="article__author-name t-p-color">Becky Pemberton</span></li><li class="article__author-list t-p-background-color__before"><span class="article__author-name t-p-color">Patrick Knox</span></li></ul></div><ul class="article__time"><li class="article__published"><span class="article__datestamp">28 Feb 2019, </span><span class="article__timestamp">15:52</span></li><li class="article__updated"><span class="article__datestamp"><span class="">Updated</span>: 28 Feb 2019, </span><span class="article__timestamp">16:02</span></li></ul></div></div></div><div class="article-switcheroo"><div class="article__content"><p class="article__content article__content--intro">THE terrorist group is widely referred to Islamic State has slaughtered thousands and has inflicted terror across the globe.</p>
<p>The group is fighting for survival after humiliating military defeats and the debate continues over the official name of ISIS, Isil or Islamic State.</p>
<figure class="article__media"><div class="article__media-img-container open-gallery" data-index="217517"><a href="#"><img alt=" There is much confusion surrounding the official name of the terror group" class="lazyload" data-src="https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000263028996.jpg" data-credit="Getty Images" data-sizes="(max-width: 375px) 335px, (max-width: 520px) 480px, 620px" data-img="https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000263028996.jpg?strip=all&amp;w=960" data-srcSet="https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000263028996.jpg?w=335 335w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000263028996.jpg?w=480 480w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000263028996.jpg?w=620 620w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000263028996.jpg?w=670 670w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000263028996.jpg?w=960 960w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000263028996.jpg?w=1240 1240w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000263028996.jpg?w=1005 1005w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000263028996.jpg?w=1440 1440w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000263028996.jpg?w=1860 1860w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000263028996.jpg?w=1340 1340w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000263028996.jpg?w=1920 1920w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000263028996.jpg?w=2480 2480w" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1.8 1&quot;%3E%3C/svg%3E"/></a><div class="article__gallery-count"><span class="article__gallery-count-value">5</span></div></div><figcaption class="article__media-caption"><span class="article__media-span"> There is much confusion surrounding the official name of the terror group</span><span class="article__credit">Credit: Getty Images</span></figcaption></figure>
<h2>What does ISIS stand for?</h2>
<p>Many people have heard of the term ISIS, which is an acronym for the Islamic State in Iraq and Syria.</p>
<p>It can also mean the Islamic State in al-Sham, the Arabic name for the region, and the group have said its goal is to create a caliphate in this region.</p>
<p>The name ISIS has proved an issue for many companies and brands, as it also belongs to an ancient Egyptian goddess.</p>
<p>The murderous network – known for its barbaric public executions – was originally part of al-Qaeda before splitting with the group over differences in ideology and methods.</p><div class="advert-wrapper advert-wrapper--outstream"><div id="outstream" class="dfp-ad advert--outstream"></div></div>
<p>It believes all Muslims should unite into a worldwide caliphate.</p>
<figure class="article__media"><div class="article__media-img-container open-gallery" data-index="217518"><a href="#"><img alt=" A propaganda photograph of an ISIS militant in Syria" class="lazyload" data-src="https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002853666022.jpg" data-credit="Alamy" data-sizes="(max-width: 375px) 335px, (max-width: 520px) 480px, 620px" data-img="https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002853666022.jpg?strip=all&amp;w=960" data-srcSet="https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002853666022.jpg?w=335 335w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002853666022.jpg?w=480 480w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002853666022.jpg?w=620 620w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002853666022.jpg?w=670 670w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002853666022.jpg?w=960 960w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002853666022.jpg?w=1240 1240w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002853666022.jpg?w=1005 1005w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002853666022.jpg?w=1440 1440w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002853666022.jpg?w=1860 1860w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002853666022.jpg?w=1340 1340w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002853666022.jpg?w=1920 1920w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002853666022.jpg?w=2480 2480w" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1.7 1&quot;%3E%3C/svg%3E"/></a><div class="article__gallery-count"><span class="article__gallery-count-value">5</span></div></div><figcaption class="article__media-caption"><span class="article__media-span"> A propaganda photograph of an ISIS militant in Syria</span><span class="article__credit">Credit: Alamy</span></figcaption></figure>
<h2>What is the meaning of Isil?</h2>
<p>Isil is an acronym standing for Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant.</p>
<p>This name was given to the group as it was thought to be more accurate to their geographical location as the Levant includes Syria, Palestine, Lebanon, Israel and Jordan.</p>
<p>Many governments and leaders, including Barack Obama and David Cameron, have used the term Isil as it is thought to be a better translation for al-Sham, which is the Arabic name for the area.</p><div class="advert-wrapper advert-wrapper--articlempu"><div id="articlempu" class="dfp-ad advert--inarticle"></div></div>
<p>In a statement released following the brutal beheading of American photojournalist James Foley, Mr Cameron’s office said: “The Prime Minister has condemned the barbaric and brutal murder of James Foley by Isil (Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant) in Syria.</p>
<p>“This will not change our commitment to tackling this appalling organisation and doing everything we can to keep our country safe.”</p>
<figure class="article__media"><div class="article__media-img-container open-gallery" data-index="217519"><a href="#"><img alt=" ISIS militants parade in 2014 in Raqqa, Syria" class="lazyload" data-src="https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002920966731.jpg" data-credit="Alamy" data-sizes="(max-width: 375px) 335px, (max-width: 520px) 480px, 620px" data-img="https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002920966731.jpg?strip=all&amp;w=960" data-srcSet="https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002920966731.jpg?w=335 335w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002920966731.jpg?w=480 480w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002920966731.jpg?w=620 620w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002920966731.jpg?w=670 670w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002920966731.jpg?w=960 960w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002920966731.jpg?w=1240 1240w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002920966731.jpg?w=1005 1005w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002920966731.jpg?w=1440 1440w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002920966731.jpg?w=1860 1860w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002920966731.jpg?w=1340 1340w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002920966731.jpg?w=1920 1920w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict0002920966731.jpg?w=2480 2480w" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 2 1&quot;%3E%3C/svg%3E"/></a><div class="article__gallery-count"><span class="article__gallery-count-value">5</span></div></div><figcaption class="article__media-caption"><span class="article__media-span"> ISIS militants parade in 2014 in Raqqa, Syria</span><span class="article__credit">Credit: Alamy</span></figcaption></figure>
<h2>What is the meaning of Daesh?</h2>
<p>The word Daesh is an acronym for al-Dawla al-Islamiya fi al-Iraq wa al-Sham.</p>
<p>The term is derived from a rough translation of Arabic words, including Arabic verb دعس, which means to tread underfoot or crush.</p>
<p>It can also be spelt DAIISH, Da&#x27;esh or Daech, and is a name which members of the terror group despise.</p>
<p>According to the <a href="https://blog.ap.org/announcements/now-we-say-the-islamic-state-group-instead-of-isil" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Associated Press</a> in 2014, ISIS threatened &quot;to cut the tongue of anyone who publicly used the acronym Daesh&quot;.</p>
<p>Following the attacks in France, the French government started adopting this term instead of ISIS or Isil.</p>
<p>Former French Foreign Minister Laurent Fabius said: “This is a terrorist group and not a state.</p>
<p>“I do not recommend using the term Islamic State because it blurs the lines between Islam, Muslims and Islamists.”</p>
<figure class="article__media"><div class="article__media-img-container open-gallery" data-index="217520"><a href="#"><img alt=" The caliph of the self-proclaimed Islamic State, Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi. He is believed to have been killed." class="lazyload" data-src="https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000120535877.jpg" data-credit="ISLAMIC STATE" data-sizes="(max-width: 375px) 335px, (max-width: 520px) 480px, 620px" data-img="https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000120535877.jpg?strip=all&amp;w=960" data-srcSet="https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000120535877.jpg?w=335 335w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000120535877.jpg?w=480 480w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000120535877.jpg?w=620 620w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000120535877.jpg?w=670 670w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000120535877.jpg?w=960 960w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000120535877.jpg?w=1240 1240w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000120535877.jpg?w=1005 1005w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000120535877.jpg?w=1440 1440w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000120535877.jpg?w=1860 1860w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000120535877.jpg?w=1340 1340w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000120535877.jpg?w=1920 1920w, https://www.thesun.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2017/01/nintchdbpict000120535877.jpg?w=2480 2480w" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 1.4 1&quot;%3E%3C/svg%3E"/></a><div class="article__gallery-count"><span class="article__gallery-count-value">5</span></div></div><figcaption class="article__media-caption"><span class="article__media-span"> The caliph of the self-proclaimed Islamic State, Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi. He is believed to have been killed.</span><span class="article__credit">Credit: ISLAMIC STATE</span></figcaption></figure>
<h2>Which is the correct name?</h2>
<p>The four competing names are just a few of the those used by the terror group, which started in 1999 when it was formed by Jordanian militant Abu Musab al-Zarqawi.</p>
<p>As far as they are concerned, the correct term is the Islamic State - but the British and US Governments are among those preferring to use the name Isil.</p>
<p>The term ISIS is more commonly used within international news publications, and has been used as a label in official United Nations reports.</p>
<p>Counter-terrorism expert Dr Anne Aly, a research fellow at Curtin University, said it is neither &quot;here or there&quot; what you call the terror group.</p>
<p>She said it is more important to note that they call themselves the Islamic State, as it shows they are trying to create a state does not respect the borders of Iraq and Syria.</p>
<p>In 2015 the BBC&#x27;s Director General refused to drop the term Islamic State from the corporation&#x27;s coverage.</p>
<p>All BBC broadcasts and reports refer to the group as the &quot;so-called Islamic State&quot;.</p>
<p>At the time a BBC spokesman said the corporation had no choice but to refer to the group by the name it uses itself.</p>
